WEBVTT

00:11.511 --> 00:13.805
♪♪

00:13.888 --> 00:16.725
NEWS ANNOUNCER: <i>Recently, there has been</i>
<i>a rash of mass murders.</i>

00:18.184 --> 00:20.979
NEWS ANNOUNCER 2: <i>Here in Los Angeles,</i>
<i>murder charges were filed today.</i>

00:21.146 --> 00:23.314
JOAN RENNER: <i>At this point, police</i>
<i>have a number</i>

00:23.398 --> 00:25.692
<i>of these serial killer cases</i>
<i>under their belt.</i>

00:26.317 --> 00:28.945
This isn't a completely
unknown animal anymore.

00:29.029 --> 00:31.990
<i>There was Rodney Alcala, William Bonin,</i>

00:32.073 --> 00:33.450
<i>The Hillside Stranglers.</i>

00:33.533 --> 00:35.410
NEWS ANNOUNCER:
<i>Now the fate of Angelo Buono</i>

00:35.493 --> 00:36.828
<i>is in the hands of the jury</i>

00:36.911 --> 00:38.913
<i>which can convict him</i>
<i>or confirm his innocence.</i>

00:38.997 --> 00:40.457
In rapid succession,

00:40.790 --> 00:42.459
<i>you had serial killer cases</i>

00:42.542 --> 00:45.253
<i>at the same court at the same time.</i>

00:46.087 --> 00:48.590
But just when things were winding down,

00:48.673 --> 00:51.426
<i>something unbelievable happened.</i>

00:52.343 --> 00:53.720
MATT MURPHY: <i>The police had no idea</i>

00:53.803 --> 00:56.264
<i>that something horrifically sadistic</i>

00:56.347 --> 00:57.557
<i>and brutal</i>

00:57.640 --> 00:59.559
was waiting on the other side of the door.

00:59.642 --> 01:04.189
(ominous music playing)

01:06.066 --> 01:10.904
(dramatic theme playing)

01:10.987 --> 01:15.158
♪♪

01:20.163 --> 01:25.210
♪♪

01:27.253 --> 01:28.880
ROBERT SOUZA: <i>Getting the Freeway Killer,</i>

01:28.963 --> 01:31.758
<i>William Bonin, off the street</i>
<i>was a big relief to us.</i>

01:33.343 --> 01:35.470
There were four accomplices
that we know about.

01:35.553 --> 01:38.389
<i>So we knew the work was really</i>
<i>just beginning</i>

01:39.140 --> 01:40.475
<i>trying to figure out</i>

01:40.558 --> 01:43.103
<i>how he was able to</i>
<i>manipulate them to do things.</i>

01:43.728 --> 01:45.230
MURPHY: <i>In June of 1980,</i>

01:45.313 --> 01:47.440
detectives, including John St. John,

01:47.524 --> 01:50.360
interrogated William Bonin
about the freeway killings

01:50.443 --> 01:51.736
and his four accomplices.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.863
These interrogations were recorded,

01:53.947 --> 01:57.867
and it is chilling to hear
how calm William Bonin is,

01:58.284 --> 01:59.702
uh, especially as he discusses

01:59.786 --> 02:02.247
how he met his accomplice, Vernon Butts.

02:03.623 --> 02:05.208
INTERVIEWER:
<i>Mr. Bonin, why don't you start</i>

02:05.291 --> 02:09.087
<i>and tell us</i>
<i>how you got started in this.</i>

02:09.879 --> 02:14.717
WILLIAM BONIN: <i>Me and Vernon were at a,</i>
<i>uh... drive-in theater.</i>

02:16.219 --> 02:18.263
<i>I initiated the conversation.</i>

02:18.847 --> 02:20.890
<i>You know, I was joking with him at first.</i>

02:21.724 --> 02:23.601
<i>And Vernon, uh... went along with it.</i>

02:23.935 --> 02:26.813
<i>You know, I was talking about picking up</i>
<i>the hitchhiker in there and having sex.</i>

02:26.896 --> 02:28.731
<i>During all this time I was going out there</i>

02:28.815 --> 02:30.650
<i>I had no intentions of killing the guy.</i>

02:31.401 --> 02:32.944
<i>You know, I looked at Vernon,</i>

02:33.027 --> 02:36.072
<i>I says "Can you go through with</i>
<i>it?" And he says "Yeah."</i>

02:36.698 --> 02:40.076
<i>I strangled him until he was</i>
<i>dead. I believe I used his shirt.</i>

02:44.330 --> 02:46.666
SOUZA: <i>Bonin was very manipulative.</i>

02:47.250 --> 02:50.170
He had kind of a mental control
over his accomplices.

02:50.253 --> 02:51.504
They were young kids.

02:51.671 --> 02:54.549
<i>They probably liked hanging out</i>
<i>with him to get booze and drugs.</i>

02:54.632 --> 02:57.760
<i>Some of these kids were very low IQs.</i>

02:58.386 --> 03:00.722
<i>Although I still think that</i>
<i>it takes a pretty evil mind</i>

03:00.805 --> 03:04.142
even to participate
or be coerced into doing that

03:04.559 --> 03:06.519
if it's not in you to begin with.

03:06.603 --> 03:08.605
It would be pretty hard
to take an honest kid

03:08.688 --> 03:10.273
<i>and get him to do things</i>
<i>that they were doing.</i>

03:13.151 --> 03:15.862
<i>So, as the trial began in the DA's office,</i>

03:15.945 --> 03:18.156
<i>we wound up actually prosecuting him</i>

03:18.239 --> 03:21.284
for ten murder cases in Los Angeles

03:21.659 --> 03:24.829
and then Orange County filed
an additional four after that.

03:24.913 --> 03:26.206
So, there were two separate trials.

03:26.789 --> 03:28.082
MURPHY: <i>William Bonin was convicted</i>

03:28.166 --> 03:29.417
<i>of first degree murder</i>

03:29.500 --> 03:32.003
for killing 14 young men.

03:32.837 --> 03:36.382
<i>Vernon Butts committed suicide</i>
<i>before his trial began.</i>

03:37.217 --> 03:39.385
Greg Miley was convicted
of first degree murder

03:39.469 --> 03:41.054
<i>and received 25 years to life.</i>

03:41.554 --> 03:44.557
<i>William Pugh was convicted</i>
<i>of voluntary manslaughter</i>

03:44.641 --> 03:46.100
<i>and got a six year sentence.</i>

03:46.476 --> 03:49.062
<i>James Munro was convicted</i>
<i>of second degree murder</i>

03:49.145 --> 03:51.648
<i>and received a sentence</i>
<i>of 15 years to life.</i>

03:52.482 --> 03:53.691
SOUZA: <i>Bonin was never charged</i>

03:53.775 --> 03:55.318
<i>with all the murders he committed.</i>

03:55.526 --> 03:57.195
<i>They always go with the strongest cases,</i>

03:57.570 --> 03:59.447
and you can only do so many life sentences

03:59.530 --> 04:00.823
and only be killed once

04:00.907 --> 04:02.784
so the DA's office,

04:02.867 --> 04:05.078
they wanted to be assured
of the prosecution.

04:05.620 --> 04:09.624
<i>I think he was responsible</i>
<i>for probably as many as 25 more.</i>

04:11.042 --> 04:13.503
William Bonin was convicted
and sentenced to death,

04:13.795 --> 04:15.838
but the death penalty was delayed

04:15.922 --> 04:17.006
and delayed and delayed

04:17.090 --> 04:19.008
as his legal team essentially tried

04:19.092 --> 04:21.636
<i>every procedural and legal means</i>

04:21.719 --> 04:22.971
<i>of keeping him alive.</i>

04:23.846 --> 04:25.723
JAMI FLOYD: <i>For the families</i>
<i>that wanted closure,</i>

04:25.807 --> 04:27.392
it was a frustrating time.

04:27.475 --> 04:30.353
Detective Souza and St. John
began to wonder

04:30.436 --> 04:32.772
if William Bonin would outlive them.

04:34.107 --> 04:35.566
SOUZA: <i>I'd been retired for several years,</i>

04:35.650 --> 04:37.986
and I went to St. John's retirement.

04:38.278 --> 04:40.321
It was one of the biggest
retirements I'd ever seen.

04:40.405 --> 04:43.074
And at that retirement,
John and I had our moment.

04:43.157 --> 04:44.909
We sat and had a drink together
and he said,

04:44.993 --> 04:46.494
"I want you to promise me something."

04:46.577 --> 04:48.162
I said, "Yeah, whatever you need, John."

04:48.955 --> 04:53.293
<i>And he said, "I have a problem</i>
<i>I might not be around</i>

04:53.710 --> 04:55.670
<i>"when they execute Bonin in San Quentin.</i>

04:56.796 --> 04:59.424
<i>"Make me a promise that</i>
<i>you will be at that execution</i>

04:59.507 --> 05:00.675
<i>"whenever it happens.</i>

05:01.759 --> 05:03.678
<i>You have to represent us as a team."</i>

05:04.804 --> 05:07.682
<i>John knew that he was dying.</i>
<i>He had cancer.</i>

05:07.765 --> 05:10.059
<i>I knew about it, but very few</i>
<i>people knew about it.</i>

05:11.060 --> 05:12.979
He said, "Now I want you
to do something for me."

05:13.062 --> 05:14.939
He said, "I want you to get up
real close to him

05:15.356 --> 05:18.735
<i>and I want you to say</i>
<i>'Adios, you son of a bitch.'"</i>

05:19.527 --> 05:21.154
<i>I said, "I'll be there, John."</i>

05:24.324 --> 05:25.950
MURPHY: <i>Across town in Hollywood,</i>

05:26.034 --> 05:28.077
<i>detectives are working a series of murders</i>

05:28.161 --> 05:30.663
<i>of prostitutes working</i>
<i>on Sunset Boulevard.</i>

05:31.539 --> 05:33.791
<i>Police had recently found three women</i>

05:33.875 --> 05:35.251
<i>who had been shot in the head</i>

05:35.335 --> 05:37.628
<i>and dumped in various parts of the Valley.</i>

05:38.087 --> 05:39.380
<i>They also found another woman</i>

05:39.464 --> 05:40.965
<i>who had been decapitated.</i>

05:41.049 --> 05:43.926
<i>Her body was found near a</i>
<i>dumpster next to a restaurant,</i>

05:44.010 --> 05:45.386
<i>but the head was still missing.</i>

05:46.387 --> 05:49.098
The one thing that all four
of these women had in common

05:49.182 --> 05:51.392
was they were all seen on the Sunset Strip

05:51.476 --> 05:52.769
<i>the night they were killed.</i>

05:59.233 --> 06:01.944
FRANK GARCIA: Back in the late '70s
and all through the '80s,

06:02.028 --> 06:03.780
this was the devil's playground,
if you will.

06:03.863 --> 06:05.281
Everybody came here.

06:05.365 --> 06:07.658
Once the sun went down
and it was nighttime,

06:07.742 --> 06:10.286
<i>the Sunset Strip took on a whole new life.</i>

06:10.703 --> 06:13.706
<i>It was like one giant block party</i>

06:14.082 --> 06:16.125
<i>that went on for almost two miles.</i>

06:16.834 --> 06:18.586
There's always bands,

06:18.669 --> 06:20.421
there's always live music.

06:20.505 --> 06:21.798
(disco music playing)

06:21.881 --> 06:23.508
<i>Everything was spectacle.</i>

06:24.258 --> 06:27.220
We're talking about late 1970s.
We're talking about the disco era.

06:27.303 --> 06:28.971
(rock music playing)

06:29.055 --> 06:31.516
<i>But you could also go out</i>
<i>and see a band like Blondie play</i>

06:31.599 --> 06:32.725
<i>at the Whiskey A Go Go.</i>

06:34.602 --> 06:37.313
<i>These were places filled with young people</i>

06:37.647 --> 06:40.108
<i>who liked to party who were</i>
<i>from all over the city.</i>

06:42.819 --> 06:46.489
It also drew the darkest of the dark.

06:48.616 --> 06:51.744
GARCIA: <i>Liquor, drugs, and sex.</i>

06:51.828 --> 06:53.496
<i>Any kind of sex you wanted.</i>

06:56.207 --> 06:58.042
<i>After looking at the killings,</i>

06:58.501 --> 06:59.544
connections were made.

07:00.545 --> 07:03.131
<i>The common thread that</i>
<i>ran through all of the victims was that</i>

07:03.214 --> 07:05.049
<i>they were always on the Strip</i>

07:06.134 --> 07:08.136
<i>and we started connecting the dots</i>

07:08.636 --> 07:11.597
<i>and lo and behold we got a serial killer</i>

07:11.681 --> 07:13.182
running on the Sunset Strip.

07:18.688 --> 07:20.231
<i>That's when the big bonanza came in,</i>

07:20.314 --> 07:22.692
<i>it was what was found in the alley.</i>

07:25.987 --> 07:27.864
Okay, that's the spot right over there.

07:27.947 --> 07:29.240
This is it right here.

07:46.174 --> 07:48.426
<i>It was in the early morning hours.</i>

07:48.509 --> 07:51.429
There was a man trying to get
into his parking garage there,

07:51.971 --> 07:54.140
and he noticed that there was
a wooden box here,

07:54.223 --> 07:55.808
kind of like a treasure chest.

07:56.309 --> 07:58.769
So, he got out to examine
the contents of the box.

07:59.604 --> 08:02.273
<i>There was panties,</i>
<i>and there was this t-shirt.</i>

08:02.899 --> 08:05.067
<i>The t-shirt said Daddy's Girl on it.</i>

08:05.985 --> 08:08.070
As he unwrapped it,
to the shock of his life,

08:08.154 --> 08:10.364
he discovered that there was
a human head in there,

08:10.448 --> 08:11.491
<i>a woman's head</i>

08:11.574 --> 08:13.659
<i>which belonged to Exxie Wilson</i>

08:14.327 --> 08:15.745
<i>from the Sizzler parking lot.</i>

08:16.162 --> 08:18.873
<i>He immediately left it alone,</i>
<i>called the police.</i>

08:21.209 --> 08:22.710
<i>The coroner shows up</i>

08:22.793 --> 08:25.963
and he sticks a thermometer
inside the head in the throat,

08:26.047 --> 08:29.050
and I think at the time
it registered 38 degrees.

08:29.884 --> 08:31.469
Which means the head had been frozen.

08:34.889 --> 08:36.599
FLOYD: <i>When police examine Exxie's head,</i>

08:36.682 --> 08:38.434
they determined that
the killer had applied

08:38.518 --> 08:39.894
makeup to her head

08:39.977 --> 08:42.230
after it had been removed from her body.

08:43.564 --> 08:46.692
MURPHY: <i>Then the head</i>
<i>was frozen to preserve it.</i>

08:47.735 --> 08:49.612
Police began to form a picture

08:49.695 --> 08:52.698
of just how perverse this killer was.

08:53.991 --> 08:55.409
LEROY OROZCO: <i>They found that the throat</i>

08:55.493 --> 08:57.787
had seminal fluid in the throat area.

08:57.870 --> 09:00.289
In our mind, it was kept as a trophy,

09:00.373 --> 09:02.041
and he had had something to do with it

09:02.124 --> 09:03.459
because of the seminal fluid.

09:03.709 --> 09:05.044
MURPHY: <i>Police were able to determine</i>

09:05.127 --> 09:08.047
<i>that Exxie Wilson had been shot</i>
<i>in the back of the head</i>

09:08.130 --> 09:09.799
with the same caliber bullet

09:09.882 --> 09:12.093
that had been used
to kill the other women.

09:12.176 --> 09:15.388
<i>Cynthia Chandler, Gina Marano,</i>
<i>and Karen Jones.</i>

09:16.556 --> 09:18.683
We had four dead bodies

09:18.766 --> 09:21.143
<i>with the same slugs from the same gun.</i>

09:22.520 --> 09:27.358
And at that point, we didn't
have a clue who could be doing this.

09:28.192 --> 09:29.402
LOUISE FARR: <i>The news came out</i>

09:29.527 --> 09:31.112
<i>that all the women who had been killed</i>

09:31.195 --> 09:33.531
<i>had been frequenting the Sunset Strip.</i>

09:33.864 --> 09:36.325
The killer came to be known as

09:36.409 --> 09:37.743
<i>the Sunset Strip Killer.</i>

09:40.496 --> 09:43.249
Police at the time
had few clues to work with,

09:43.332 --> 09:46.252
<i>so they decided to go</i>
<i>to the media for help.</i>

09:48.421 --> 09:51.841
DETECTIVE: <i>We are requesting</i>
<i>if anyone has any knowledge</i>

09:52.633 --> 09:57.013
<i>about this box or has ever seen</i>
<i>a box like this,</i>

09:57.722 --> 10:01.225
<i>that they contact the</i>
<i>Los Angeles Police Department.</i>

10:06.188 --> 10:10.484
FARR: <i>It was June 30th</i>
<i>when hunters in a ravine near Sylmar</i>

10:10.568 --> 10:13.738
came across the mummified body
of a young woman.

10:13.821 --> 10:16.490
<i>She was later identified as Marnett Comer.</i>

10:16.574 --> 10:17.992
<i>She was only 17.</i>

10:18.367 --> 10:22.079
Marnett Comer was
a runaway from Sacramento

10:22.163 --> 10:25.291
and was working as a prostitute
like some of the other victims.

10:25.791 --> 10:28.294
<i>Police heard reports</i>
<i>that Comer was last seen</i>

10:28.377 --> 10:31.130
<i>wearing a pink t-shirt</i>
<i>that said "Daddy's Girl."</i>

10:32.632 --> 10:34.675
The t-shirt that said "Daddy's Girl"

10:34.759 --> 10:37.720
<i>had been found wrapped</i>
<i>around Exxie Wilson's head.</i>

10:40.389 --> 10:42.808
FLOYD: <i>So, now there's evidence</i>
<i>from one crime scene</i>

10:42.892 --> 10:44.935
showing up at another crime scene.

10:45.436 --> 10:49.106
<i>There wasn't much doubt now</i>
<i>that all of these murders were linked.</i>

10:51.484 --> 10:54.236
It became clear that the Sunset Killer

10:54.320 --> 10:56.822
was keeping souvenirs from his victims.

10:58.658 --> 11:01.327
GARCIA: <i>When they did</i>
<i>the autopsy on her skull,</i>

11:01.410 --> 11:04.789
she too had been shot
in the back portion of her head

11:05.414 --> 11:07.500
with a small caliber gun
which turned out to be

11:07.583 --> 11:09.126
a .25 caliber Raven,

11:09.210 --> 11:12.046
<i>the same gun that had killed</i>
<i>the other four girls.</i>

11:12.129 --> 11:14.715
FLOYD: <i>The fact that</i>
<i>all five victims were killed</i>

11:14.799 --> 11:17.134
<i>with the same gun</i>
<i>was helpful to the police,</i>

11:17.218 --> 11:19.970
<i>but it didn't actually</i>
<i>bring them any closer</i>

11:20.054 --> 11:21.764
<i>to solving the case.</i>

11:21.847 --> 11:25.059
They still had no idea where the
victims had been murdered

11:25.142 --> 11:29.814
or what to do to keep
the killer from killing again.

11:29.897 --> 11:31.816
Police were also left wondering

11:31.899 --> 11:33.651
why most of the victims were shot

11:33.734 --> 11:35.653
in the left side
of the back of their heads.

11:36.487 --> 11:38.072
<i>What was the significance of this?</i>

11:38.155 --> 11:40.991
<i>Could this help explain</i>
<i>who the killer was?</i>

11:46.330 --> 11:48.499
GARCIA: <i>The whole month of July went by</i>

11:48.582 --> 11:51.210
<i>with really no new activity,</i>

11:51.293 --> 11:53.170
no new bodies turning up

11:53.838 --> 11:55.881
<i>until August the 9th.</i>

11:55.965 --> 11:58.175
FLOYD: <i>Some residents</i>
<i>in the San Fernando Valley</i>

11:58.259 --> 12:00.970
<i>called to complain about</i>
<i>a van left on their street</i>

12:01.053 --> 12:03.472
and a really terrible odor.

12:03.889 --> 12:05.516
It was a terrible sight.

12:08.477 --> 12:10.020
<i>They unlocked the van,</i>

12:10.604 --> 12:13.858
<i>and you couldn't see</i>
<i>through the glass of the van</i>

12:13.941 --> 12:16.318
<i>because the flies were so thick.</i>

12:17.570 --> 12:21.240
And in the back of the van was
a male body with no head on it.

12:25.745 --> 12:27.747
<i>There were stab wounds</i>

12:27.830 --> 12:29.999
<i>to the buttocks, to the back,</i>

12:30.458 --> 12:31.917
<i>uh, to the anal area.</i>

12:32.251 --> 12:34.003
<i>There was no gunshot wounds</i>

12:34.962 --> 12:36.630
<i>anywhere on the body.</i>

12:37.465 --> 12:40.342
During the investigation at the van,

12:40.426 --> 12:42.636
<i>officers found a shell casing.</i>

12:43.429 --> 12:46.849
<i>That shell casing came back</i>
<i>to a .25 caliber pistol.</i>

12:49.101 --> 12:50.478
The murder of this individual,

12:50.561 --> 12:52.646
of course, sparked a lot
of interest from the media.

12:53.689 --> 12:55.900
<i>Now you got two bodies in the Valley,</i>

12:55.983 --> 12:57.401
<i>both decapitated</i>

12:57.485 --> 12:59.028
<i>and people were making the assumption</i>

12:59.111 --> 13:00.154
<i>or trying to come up with,</i>

13:00.237 --> 13:01.947
<i>well, maybe they're related.</i>

13:02.782 --> 13:04.408
MURPHY: <i>Even if this case was connected,</i>

13:04.492 --> 13:06.035
why would he kill a man?

13:06.118 --> 13:08.245
All of the victims up to this
point have been women.

13:08.662 --> 13:10.915
This person was identified as Jack Murray

13:12.208 --> 13:14.043
<i>who was a singer</i>

13:14.710 --> 13:16.587
<i>at the Little Nashville bar</i>

13:16.670 --> 13:18.589
<i>that was not too far from there.</i>

13:18.964 --> 13:21.967
<i>He was Australian and kind of a player.</i>

13:23.302 --> 13:25.763
Two days after
Jack Murray's body was found,

13:25.846 --> 13:28.557
LAPD received a call
from Valley Medical Center.

13:29.975 --> 13:32.937
<i>One of the nurses there,</i>
<i>a woman named Carol Bundy,</i>

13:33.020 --> 13:34.855
<i>was acting very strange.</i>

13:35.523 --> 13:38.400
Carol was making statements
to her coworkers

13:38.484 --> 13:41.821
